    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! Are you looking for a reliable ride that\u2019s ready for your next adventure? I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty car, and it\u2019s in really solid shape! It\u2019s been well-loved, runs like a charm, and is just waiting for someone new to get behind the wheel. Whether you're commuting to work or heading out on a weekend road trip, this beauty won't let you down. It\u2019s got a lot of life left in it and is super clean. Come take it for a spin and see for yourself\u2014I think you\u2019re going to love it!",
      "price": 33500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 23
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and the factory M-Variable locking differential, ensuring precise torque distribution. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement and a proactive rod bearing service. The chassis remains taut with upgraded Bilstein dampers and refreshed bushings, maintaining the model's signature steering rack feedback. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response are exceptionally sharp. This is a driver-spec example optimized for longitudinal dynamics and balanced lateral grip.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 23
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
